President Muhammadu Buhari has postponed his campaign rally to Zamfara state, slated for Sunday, Daily Trust reports. The postponement is being linked to the crisis rocking the All Progressives Congress (APC) in the State. The Independent National Electoral Commission (INEC) had on Friday released the final list of candidates for the March 2, this year Governorship and State House of Assembly election without that of APC in Zamfara. Presidential Spokesperson, Femi Adesina confirmed the postponement. Details soon Kebbi APC rally: Laughter as Amaechi races to podium at campaign ground Former Kaduna speaker leads others to APC as Buhari arrives Kaduna Killings: Visit Zamfara before Akwa Ibom rally, Shehu Sani tells Buhari